// Try to keep colors consistent among types of books.&lt;br /&gt;
// TYPE is the skill type required to read, or trained via reading; see skill.h&lt;br /&gt;
// LEV is the skill level you can be brought to by this book; if your skill is&lt;br /&gt;
//  already at LEV or higher, you may enjoy the book but won't learn anything.&lt;br /&gt;
// REQ is the skill level required to read this book, at all. If you lack the&lt;br /&gt;
//  required skill level, you'll waste 10 (?) turns then quit.&lt;br /&gt;
// FUN is the fun had by reading;&lt;br /&gt;
// INT is an intelligence requirement.&lt;br /&gt;
// TIME is the time, in minutes (10 turns), taken to gain the fun/skill bonus.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
#define BOOK(name,rarity,price,color,mat1,mat2,volume,wgt,melee_dam,to_hit,\&lt;br /&gt;
type,level,req,fun,intel,time,des) \&lt;br /&gt;
	index++;itypes.push_back(new it_book(index,rarity,price,name,des,'?',\&lt;br /&gt;
color,mat1,mat2,volume,wgt,melee_dam,0,to_hit,0,type,level,req,fun,intel,time))&lt;br /&gt;
